Test Name: Chlamydia trachomatis, Self-Collect, Amplified RNA, Vaginal
Purpose: To detect Chlamydia trachomatis RNA in self-collected vaginal specimens for diagnosis of infection.
Container: Vaginal swab in appropriate transport media tube
Equipment: Automated nucleic acid extractor and real-time PCR instrument (e.g., Roche cobas 4800/z 480 or Hologic Panther)
